House Bill 116 (AS PASSED HOUSE AND SENATE)
By: Representatives McDonald III of the 26th, Crowe of the 118th, Hitchens of the 161st,
Lumsden of the 12th, and Barrett of the 24th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 5 of Chapter 2 of Title 35 and Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to Motor Carrier Compliance Division of the Department of Public
3 Safety and motor vehicles and traffic, respectively, so as to change the name of the Motor
4 Carrier Compliance Division of the Department of Public Safety to Commercial Vehicle
5 Enforcement; to require law enforcement officers within such division be trained, sworn, and
6 certified; to provide for conforming changes; to provide for related matters; to repeal
7 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 Article 5 of Chapter 2 of Title 35 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
11 Motor Carrier Compliance Division of the Department of Public Safety, is amended by
12 revising Code Section 35-2-100, relating to creation and members designated as law
13 enforcement officers, as follows:
14 "35-2-100.
15 There shall be created and established a division of the Department of Public Safety to be
16 known as the Motor Carrier Compliance Division Commercial Vehicle Enforcement, and
