17 within the division shall be created a section to be known as the Motor Carrier
18 Regulatory Compliance Enforcement Section. Except as provided in Code Section
19 35-2-102, the members of the Motor Carrier Compliance Enforcement Section Commercial
20 Vehicle Enforcement shall be known, and designated, trained, sworn, and certified as 'law
21 enforcement officers.'"
22 SECTION 2.
23 Said article is further amended in Code Section 35-2-101, relating to jurisdiction, duties and
24 powers, and use of dogs to detect controlled substances, by revising subsection (a), the
25 introductory language of subsection (b), and subsection (d) as follows:
26 "(a) The Motor Carrier Compliance Enforcement Section Commercial Vehicle
27 Enforcement division of the department shall have jurisdiction throughout this state with
28 such duties and powers as are prescribed by law.
29 (b) The primary duties of the division of Commercial Vehicle Enforcement Motor Carrier
30 Compliance Enforcement Section shall be as follows:"
31 "(d) The commissioner shall authorize law enforcement officers of the Motor Carrier
32 Compliance Enforcement Section Commercial Vehicle Enforcement to make use of dogs
33 trained for the purpose of detection of drugs and controlled substances while such officers
34 are engaged in the performance of their authorized duties. If such authorized use of such
35 a dog indicates probable cause to indicate the presence of contraband, the officer or officers
36 shall in those circumstances have the full authority of peace officers to enforce the
37 provisions of Article 2 of Chapter 13 of Title 16, the 'Georgia Controlled Substances Act,'
38 and Article 3 of Chapter 13 of Title 16, the 'Dangerous Drug Act'; provided, however, that
39 the department must immediately notify the local law enforcement agency and district
40 attorney of the jurisdiction where a seizure is made."
