41 SECTION 3.
42 Said article is further amended by revising Code Section 35-2-102, relating to weight
43 inspector positions, training, powers and responsibilities, and presence of certified peace
44 officer, as follows:
45 "35-2-102.
46 (a) The commissioner is authorized to establish a position to be known as 'weight
47 inspector' within the Motor Carrier Compliance Enforcement Section of the Department
48 of Public Safety Commercial Vehicle Enforcement division of the department. Weight
49 inspectors shall be assigned to fixed scales facilities and shall not be authorized to operate
50 outside such facilities. The number of such positions shall be determined by the
51 commissioner within the limits set by available appropriations. Weight inspectors may be
52 divided into such ranks as the commissioner deems appropriate.
53 (b) The commissioner shall ensure that a weight inspector is properly trained regarding
54 laws governing commercial motor vehicle weight, registration, size, and load, including,
55 but not limited to, commercial motor vehicle provisions in Article 2 of Chapter 6 of
56 Title 32 and safety standards for commercial motor vehicles and such motor vehicle
57 components. The training required in the areas required by this subsection shall be
58 equivalent to training provided to certified officers in the Motor Carrier Compliance
59 Enforcement Section Commercial Vehicle Enforcement.
60 (c) A weight inspector, at the a fixed scales facility, shall be authorized to:
61 (1) Enforce noncriminal provisions relating to commercial motor vehicle weight,
62 registration, size, and load and assess a civil penalty for a violation of such provisions;
63 and
64 (2) Detain a commercial motor vehicle that:
65 (A) Has a safety defect which is critical to the continued safe operation of the vehicle;
66 (B) Is being operated in violation of any criminal law; or
