67 (C) Is being operated in violation of an out-of-service order as reported on the federal
68 Safety and Fitness Electronic Records data base.
69 The detention authorized by this paragraph shall be for the purpose of contacting a
70 certified member of the Motor Carrier Compliance Enforcement Section or Commercial
71 Vehicle Enforcement or the Georgia State Patrol. A certified officer shall report to the
72 scene of a detained vehicle and take any further action deemed appropriate, including
73 completing the inspection and investigation, making an arrest, or bringing criminal or
74 civil charges.
75 (d) At all times while a weight inspector is on duty, there shall be a supervisor over the
76 weight inspector also on duty who shall be a certified peace officer."
77 SECTION 4.
78 Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to motor vehicles and traffic, is
79 amended by revising Code Section 40-1-52, relating to establishment of Motor Carrier
80 Compliance Division, as follows:
81 "40-1-52.
82 There is created and established a division within the Department of Public Safety to be
83 known as the Motor Carrier Compliance Division Commercial Vehicle Enforcement which
84 shall include a section designated the Regulatory Compliance Section. Except as provided
85 in Chapter 2 of Title 35, the sworn members of the Motor Carrier Compliance Division
86 Commercial Vehicle Enforcement shall be known and designated as law enforcement
87 officers. The Regulatory Compliance Section shall be responsible for the regulation of the
88 operation of motor carriers and limousine carriers in accordance with this article, Code
89 Section 40-1-8, and Article 2 of this chapter."
