90 SECTION 5.
91 Said title is further amended by revising Code Section 40-2-82, relating to license plates for
92 Department of Public Safety vehicles operated by Georgia State Patrol or Motor Carrier
93 Compliance Division, as follows:
94 "40-2-82.
95 The commissioner of public safety shall be issued distinctive license plates to be used on
96 motor vehicles assigned to the Department of Public Safety and operated by troopers of the
97 Georgia State Patrol or law enforcement officers of the Motor Carrier Compliance Division
98 Commercial Vehicle Enforcement. The distinctive plates shall be issued free of charge in
99 accordance with procedures agreed upon by the commissioner of public safety and the state
100 revenue commissioner. License plates issued pursuant to this Code section need not
101 contain a place for the county name decal and no county name decal need be affixed to a
102 license plate issued pursuant to this Code section."
103 SECTION 6.
104 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
